Another prompt-based attack method, LoFT (Local Fine-T uning of proxy public models), leverages public models as proxies to approximate the private targeted models [178]. The hypothesis is that the attacks are transferable, thus the success of the attack highly depends on how well the proxy model can approximate the targeted private model within the lexico-semantic neighborhood of the harmful queries. Furthermore, several platforms (e.g., PromptBase [158]) have emerged to buy and sell malicious prompts as marketplace products. These platforms may produce attack-intended prompts upon request from malicious clients. Although these methods have shown their potential for successful attacks, they have some limitations in various aspects. First, several methods, such as HOUYI [121] and AutoPrompt [187], have demonstrated their efficacy on LM/LLM-integrated applications or relatively smaller-scale LLMs but not directly on the LLMs themselves. Second, SQL-based attacks [155] are now outdated compared with recent advanced attack techniques. Third, attack methods that perform well without countermeasures [187] may not achieve similar attack success in the presence of defense techniques [215] in that environment. Fourth, optimizing the malicious prompt (e.g., JudgeDeceiver [185]) or crafting efficient prompts (e.g., HOUYI [121]) is the most crucial part of a successful prompt injection attack.
4.1.2 Jailbreaking Attack. In LLMs, “jailbreak” denotes the procedure of bypassing the predefined constraints and limitations imposed on these models [124]. It aims to deceive the LLM via instructions to breach the basic safety restrictions set by its developers. Jailbreaking allows for generating outputs that may contain toxic, manipulative, racist, illegal suggestions or offensive content. Nevertheless, it is essential to recognize that jailbreaking can introduce ethical and legal dilemmas, as it may breach intellectual property rights or employ LLMs in manners that are not sanctioned by the developers. As demonstrated in Figure 6, when ChatGPT was asked to give instructions for an unethical task, it refused. However, when it was asked in a tricky way (character role-play), it responded accordingly.
